The paper deals with power control and sum-rate scaling laws for a distributed cognitive uplink, which involves communication between primary and secondary users. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of multiuser diversity, which is a common technique in wireless communication systems and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with system-level optimization and control, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses fading models, which are commonly used in multimedia communication systems (cs.MM).
